meta-application
============

This layer provides some useful applications, including some demo applications.
You can develop your applications based on our frameworks, and integrate them in this layer.

Dependencies
============

This layer depends on:
    <repo>/meta-yp/meta

The <repo> is the repository path of your AliOS Things Linux Edition.

How to build
============

Add this layer into your bblayer.conf, e.g.
    BBLAYERS ?= " \
        <repo>/meta-yp/meta \
        <repo>/meta-yp/meta-openembedded/meta-oe \
        <repo>/meta-yp/meta-openembedded/meta-perl \
        <repo>/meta-yp/meta-openembedded/meta-python \
        <repo>/meta-yp/meta-openembedded/meta-networking \
        <repo>/meta-core/meta-base \
        <repo>/meta-application \
        "

Contents
============

helloworld
------------
A helloworld application, it printes a "hello world" message in endless loop at intervals of 9s.

This recipe provides a demo to you about how to write a recipe (yocto bb).


